de.unihannover.se.iviewxjava.core.receiver

Class ETReceiver<E extends ChronologicComparable<E>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.unihannover.se.iviewxjava.core.receiver.ETReceiver<E>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ETEventReceiver, ETPlaybackReceiver, ETSampleReceiver

    public abstract class ETReceiver<E extends ChronologicComparable<E>>
extends Object
    This class provides a skeletal implementation of a Receiver that fetches chronologically ordered data.

    To implement a ETReceiver, the programmer needs to extend this class and provide an implementation for the getNextFromSource method.

    • Method Detail

      • getNextFromSource

        protected abstract ETResponse<E> getNextFromSource()
        Returns the next item from the data source wrapped in a ETResponse.

        This method has to be implemented by the subclass. This abstract class will use it as part of the template method pattern.

        Returns:
        Next data item wrapped in a ETResponse

      • getNext

        public ETResponse<E> getNext()
        Returns the next item from the data source wrapped in a ETResponse. If the item in the response is not null, it will be stabilized according to the currently set ETStabilizationStrategy.
        Returns:
        Next stabilized data item wrapped in a ETResponse

      • setStabilizationStrategy

        public void setStabilizationStrategy(ETStabilizationStrategy<E> strategy)
        Sets the stabilization strategy.

        Stabilization strategies correct the returned data by applying a correcting algorithm to the retrieved item before returning it.

        Parameters:
        strategy - Stabilization strategy
